Integrating python IDE in Sublime Text 3
#
1. Install Package Control
2. Install SublimeREPL package
3. Create "New Build System" in Tools:
Sublime Text 3\Packages\User\PythonREPL.sublime-build
	{
  	   "target": "run_existing_window_command", 
 	   "id": "repl_python_run",
  	   "file": "config/Python/Main.sublime-menu",
	}

4. Create user "Key_Bindings" in "Preferences" for starting interactive interpreter
Sublime Text 3\Packages\User\user.sublime-keymap
[
	{ 
	"keys": ["ctrl+f10"],
	"command": "repl_transfer_current",
	"args": {"scope": "file"}
	},

	{
	"keys": ["ctrl+f11"],
	"command": "repl_open",
	"args": {"cmd": ["python", "-u", "-i", "$file_basename"],
	 		 "cwd": "$file_path",
	 		 "encoding": "utf8",
			 "extend_env": {"PYTHONIOENCODING": "utf-8"},
	 		 "external_id": "python",
	 		 "syntax": "Packages/Python/Python.tmLanguage",
	 		 "type": "subprocess"} 
	},

	{ 
	"keys": ["ctrl+shift+c"], 
	"command": "cancel_build"
	},
]

5. More Sublime Text 3 Packages:
	"Package Control",		
	"Anaconda",
	"SideBarEnhancements",
	"AutoFileName",
	"PySide",
6. Color Schemes, themes
	"Atomic Color Scheme",
	"Color Scheme - Vintage Terminal",
